'''輪藻綱'''（學名：{{lang|la|Charophyceae}}），又名'''車軸藻綱'''，舊屬[[綠藻門|綠藻門]]，今屬[[車軸藻門|車軸藻門]]。

它的分類地位仍有爭議。有些[[植物學|植物學家]]認為可以將[[輪藻門|輪藻門]]和[[綠藻門|綠藻門]]納入[[植物界|植物界]]中<ref name = "Campbell">Campbell, N. A. & Reece, J. B.  2005.  ''Biology, Seventh Edition''.  Benjamin Cummings, San Francisco.</ref>，但有些植物學家認為輪藻綱被編入[[綠藻門|綠藻門]]、[[鏈形植物門|鏈形植物門]]，或是[[鏈型植物|鏈型植物]]下界<ref name = "Hoek">Hoek, C. van den, Mann, D. G. & Jahns, H. M. 1995.  [http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=xuUoiFesSHMC&printsec=frontcover ''Algae: An Introduction to Phycology''] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=xuUoiFesSHMC&printsec=frontcover |date=20141101212714 }}.  Cambridge University Press, Cambridge. ISBN 0-521-30419-9</ref><ref>[[Streptophytina|Streptophytina]]</ref><ref name = "Tolweb">McCourt, R. M., Chapman, R. L., Buchheim, M. & Mishler, B. D. [http://tolweb.org/Green_plants/2382 “Green Plants”] {{Wayback|url=http://tolweb.org/Green_plants/2382 |date=20170711071552 }}.  Accessed 13 December 2007</ref>，其他[[系統分類學|系統分類學家]]把輪藻綱分在輪藻門之下，因為輪藻綱與綠藻門仍有明顯的差異<ref name = "AlgaeBase">Guiry, M.D. & Guiry, G.M. 2007. AlgaeBase. World-wide electronic publication, National University of Ireland, Galway. [http://www.algaebase.org AlgaeBase.org] {{Wayback|url=http://www.algaebase.org/ |date=20091012183548 }}; searched on 13 December 2007</ref>。

且不論輪藻綱的真實分類，大多數植物學者都同意輪藻是最接近[[有胚植物|有胚植物]]（陸生植物）的一種生物<ref name = "Campbell"/><ref name="Delwiche">Delwiche, C. F. [http://www.life.umd.edu/labs/delwiche/Charophyte.htm “Charophycean Green Algae”]{{dead link|date=2018年1月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}.  Accessed 13 December 2007</ref>。不管在生殖、光合作用、cpDNA（[[葉綠體|葉綠體]]的[[DNA|DNA]]）的分析，還是其他特徵，都顯示有胚植物是由輪藻演化而成<ref name = "Campbell"/><ref name = "Laval">Turmel, M., Otis, C. & Lemieux, C.  2005.  [http://www.biomedcentral.com/1741-7007/3/22 The Complete Chloroplast DNA Sequences of the Charophycean Green Algae ''Staurastrum'' and ''Zygnema'' Reveal that the Chloroplast Genome Underwent Extensive Changes During the Evolution of the Zygnematales].  <u>BMC Biology</u> 3:22</ref>。

